---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Applied Intuition | Work Experience | Sam Lee" description="Technical Artist work at Applied Intuition, developing simulation and visualization tools for autonomous vehicle development.">
  <!-- Password Gate -->
  <div id="password-gate" class="container py-12 md:py-16">
    <div class="max-w-md mx-auto text-center">
      <img src="/images/logos/applied_intuition_inc_logo.jpeg" alt="Applied Intuition logo" class="w-20 h-20 object-contain mx-auto mb-6 rounded-2xl" />
      <h1 class="text-2xl font-display font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 mb-2">Password Required</h1>
      <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-8">This content is protected. Please enter the password to continue.</p>

      <form id="password-form" class="space-y-4">
        <input
          type="password"
          id="password-input"
          class="w-full px-4 py-3 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 rounded-xl focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-accent/50 focus:border-accent transition-all"
          placeholder="Enter password"
          autocomplete="off"
        />
        <p id="password-error" class="hidden text-red-500 text-sm">Incorrect password. Please try again.</p>
        <button type="submit" class="w-full btn-primary">
          Unlock Content
        </button>
      </form>

      <a href="/work-experience" class="inline-flex items-center mt-6 text-sm text-gray-500 hover:text-accent transition-colors">
        <svg class="w-4 h-4 mr-1" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 19l-7-7 7-7" />
        </svg>
        Back to Work Experience
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Protected Content (hidden by default) -->
  <section id="protected-content" class="hidden container py-12 md:py-16">
    <header class="mb-12">
      <nav class="mb-6">
        <a href="/work-experience" class="inline-flex items-center text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 hover:text-accent transition-colors">
          <svg class="w-4 h-4 mr-1" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 19l-7-7 7-7" />
          </svg>
          Back to Work Experience
        </a>
      </nav>

      <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
        <img src="/images/logos/applied_intuition_inc_logo.jpeg" alt="Applied Intuition logo" class="w-16 h-16 object-contain flex-shrink-0 rounded-2xl" />
        <div>
          <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Applied Intuition</h1>
          <p class="text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">Technical Artist</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 dark:text-gray-500">February 2023 – June 2024</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
        I joined Applied Intuition as a Technical Artist in February 2023, developing simulation and visualization tools
        for autonomous vehicle development. I worked at the intersection of real-time graphics, engineering, and product
        design to build systems that help AV engineers create and test virtual environments.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div>

      <!-- Project: Material Editing System -->
      <article class="mb-16">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 mb-2">Material Editing System</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 dark:text-gray-500 mb-4">2023 – 2024</p>

        <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert mb-6">
          <p>
            Designed and built a full-stack material editing system inside Applied Intuition's sensor simulation product,
            allowing AV engineers to programmatically customize road surfaces, markings, and material properties in virtual
            environments. The system gives sensor manufacturers and software teams the ability to quickly generate varied
            synthetic training data and test specific reflectance values without manual 3D editing.
          </p>
          <p>
            I owned the project end-to-end: designing the API, building the Unreal Engine backend, and — after the PM
            requested a frontend — learning React in four weeks to ship a GUI that lets users browse material presets and
            fine-tune parameters in-product.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-8 mb-8">
          <div>
            <video
              src="/images/work-experiences/applied%20intuition/parking_materials_with_GUI_2x.mp4"
              class="w-full rounded-lg"
              controls
              autoplay
              loop
              muted
              playsinline
            ></video>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-2">Material editing GUI — users can browse presets and fine-tune parameters in real time</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <video
              src="/images/work-experiences/applied%20intuition/parking_lot_surface_materials.mp4"
              class="w-full rounded-lg"
              controls
              autoplay
              loop
              muted
              playsinline
            ></video>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-2">Surface material variants applied to a parking lot environment</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <video
              src="/images/work-experiences/applied%20intuition/realistic_material_editng2.mp4"
              class="w-full rounded-lg"
              controls
              autoplay
              loop
              muted
              playsinline
            ></video>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-2">Realistic material editing — adjusting reflectance and surface properties</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-8">
          <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 rounded-full text-sm">Unreal Engine</span>
          <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 rounded-full text-sm">C++</span>
          <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 rounded-full text-sm">HLSL</span>
          <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 rounded-full text-sm">React</span>
          <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 rounded-full text-sm">YAML</span>
          <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 rounded-full text-sm">Sensor Simulation</span>
        </div>

        <h4 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 mb-3">Contributions</h4>
        <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert">
          <ul>
            <li><strong>API design</strong> — Designed a future-proof, extendable API that lets users select objects, choose material presets, and fine-tune parameters without locking into specific engine internals</li>
            <li><strong>Unreal backend</strong> — Implemented the material editing pipeline in C++, connecting user-facing controls to Unreal's material system and shaders</li>
            <li><strong>React frontend</strong> — Learned React in four weeks and partnered with frontend engineering to build a GUI leveraging the product's YAML-to-GUI feature, significantly improving usability</li>
            <li><strong>XFN collaboration</strong> — Gathered input from users, TAs, engineers, and designers to find the right balance between flexibility and guard rails</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </article>

      <!-- Project: Custom Streetlights -->
      <article class="mb-16">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 mb-2">Custom Streetlights</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 dark:text-gray-500 mb-4">2023 – 2024</p>

        <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert mb-6">
          <p>
            Built a system that allows users to programmatically customize streetlights in parking lot simulation scenes.
            The project was driven by a customer need: nighttime environments with minimal lighting are a known challenge
            for autonomous vehicle perception systems, and teams needed a way to reliably generate and control those
            conditions at scale.
          </p>
          <p>
            The streetlight system gives users direct control over placement, intensity, color temperature, and coverage,
            enabling repeatable nighttime test scenarios for sensor validation and AV software training.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-8 mb-8">
          <div>
            <video
              src="/images/work-experiences/applied%20intuition/global_street_light_demo.mov"
              class="w-full rounded-lg"
              controls
              autoplay
              loop
              muted
              playsinline
            ></video>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-2">Streetlight customization system — programmatic control over placement and lighting parameters</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <video
              src="/images/work-experiences/applied%20intuition/parking_lot_night_rain.mp4"
              class="w-full rounded-lg"
              controls
              autoplay
              loop
              muted
              playsinline
            ></video>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-2">Nighttime parking lot with rain — a challenging scenario for autonomous perception systems</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-8">
          <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 rounded-full text-sm">Unreal Engine</span>
          <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 rounded-full text-sm">C++</span>
          <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 rounded-full text-sm">HLSL</span>
          <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 rounded-full text-sm">Sensor Simulation</span>
          <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 rounded-full text-sm">Lighting</span>
        </div>

        <h4 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 mb-3">Contributions</h4>
        <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert">
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Programmatic lighting control</strong> — Built a system for scripting streetlight properties (placement, intensity, color temperature, spread) across scenes without manual in-editor editing</li>
            <li><strong>Nighttime scenario support</strong> — Enabled customers to generate repeatable low-light test conditions that are critical for validating AV perception in challenging environments</li>
            <li><strong>Unreal content pipeline</strong> — Developed C++ tooling to maintain performance and visual quality standards for real-world simulation fidelity</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </article>

    </div>
  </section>

  <script is:inline>
    // Correct password (you can change this)
    const CORRECT_PASSWORD = 'letmein';

    function showContent() {
      document.getElementById('password-gate').classList.add('hidden');
      document.getElementById('protected-content').classList.remove('hidden');
      sessionStorage.setItem('ai_authenticated', 'true');
    }

    function checkPassword(password) {
      return password.toLowerCase().trim() === CORRECT_PASSWORD;
    }

    // Check if coming from work experience page with password
    const storedPassword = sessionStorage.getItem('ai_password');
    if (storedPassword && checkPassword(storedPassword)) {
      showContent();
      sessionStorage.removeItem('ai_password');
    }

    // Check if already authenticated
    if (sessionStorage.getItem('ai_authenticated') === 'true') {
      showContent();
    }

    // Handle form submission
    document.getElementById('password-form').addEventListener('submit', function(e) {
      e.preventDefault();
      const input = document.getElementById('password-input');
      const error = document.getElementById('password-error');

      if (checkPassword(input.value)) {
        showContent();
      } else {
        error.classList.remove('hidden');
        input.classList.add('border-red-300');
        input.value = '';
        input.focus();
      }
    });
  </script>
</BaseLayout>
